==English==

===Adjective===
'''companionable'''

# Pertaining to the quality of friendliness or sociability. 
#:'''1847''' ''She returned presently, bringing a smoking basin and a basket of work; and, having placed the former on the hob, drew in her seat, evidently pleased to find me so '''companionable'''.'' — Emily Bronte, ''Wuthering Heights'', [[s:Wuthering Heights/Chapter IV|Chapter 4]].

